com.here.android.mpa.urbanmobility

Class CarOptions

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.here.android.mpa.urbanmobility.CarOptions

  • public abstract class CarOptions
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents common options specific for car based sections (like taxi or car share).

    IMPORTANT: Urban Mobility routing is a Beta feature. The related classes are subject to change without notice.

    Audience:
    internal

      • setMaxCount

        public CarOptions setMaxCount(int value)
        Specifies the maximum number of car connections to be included in the response. Allowed range is [1, 6] or -1. Using unsupported value will result error response in route calculation. The default is 3.
        Parameters:
        value - maximum number of connections to be included in the response, or -1 to use default value
        Returns:
        The modified CarOptions itself.

      • setMinDistance

        public CarOptions setMinDistance(int value)
        Sets minimum allowed distance in meters, for car. Allowed range is [500, 100000] or -1 to use default. Using unsupported value will result error response in route calculation. The default is 500.
        Parameters:
        value - minimum allowed distance in meters, or -1 to use default

        The modified CarOptions itself.
